            <h2>Course Lessons</h2>
            <p>This course is designed to help you manage your time effectively and increase productivity. Below are the lessons included in this course:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>Lesson 1: Understanding Time Management</strong>
                    <p>Learn the fundamentals of time management, why it is important, and how it can benefit your personal and professional life.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Lesson 2: Setting SMART Goals</strong>
                    <p>Discover how to set Specific, Measurable, Achievable, Relevant, and Time-bound goals to maximize your productivity.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Lesson 3: Prioritizing Tasks</strong>
                    <p>Understand different prioritization techniques such as the Eisenhower Matrix to help you focus on what truly matters.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Lesson 4: Creating a Schedule</strong>
                    <p>Learn how to create an effective schedule that balances work, personal time, and rest.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Lesson 5: Overcoming Procrastination</strong>
                    <p>Identify the root causes of procrastination and learn strategies to overcome it.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Lesson 6: Productivity Tools & Techniques</strong>
                    <p>Explore various tools and techniques such as Pomodoro Technique, time blocking, and productivity apps to enhance your efficiency.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Lesson 7: Reviewing & Reflecting</strong>
                    <p>Understand the importance of regular reviews and reflections to continuously improve your time management skills.</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
